===Etymology===
Late 19th Century, from ''pneumon'' (Greek) 'lung' + ''-o-'' + ''ultra'' (Latin) 'beyond' + ''microscopic'' + ''silico-'' 'silicon' + ''volcano'' + ''konis'' 'dust' + ''-osis'' 'disease'.

===Noun===
'''pneumonoultramicroscopicsilicovolcanoconiosis'''

# A hypothetical, invented [[disease]] of the lungs, caused by inhaling mineral or metallic dust, such as [[silicon]] and [[quartzite]], over a long [[period]].  Usually used only as an example of one of the longest English words, at 45 letters it is the longest word in the Oxford English Dictionary
#:Often shortened to [[pneumonoconiosis]] or [[pneumoconiosis]].

